WLC_LOG_SET_HANDLER(3)                                   WLC CORE API FUNCTIONS

NAME

    wlc_log_set_handler - provides for a callback to a custom log handler

SYNOPSIS
     
    void wlc_log_set_handler(void (*cb)(enum wlc_log_type type, const char *str));

DESCRIPTION

    wlc_log_set_handler() allows for the use of a custom log handler if the
    project requires it.  Without a handler configured wlc will not produce any
    output.  The argument of wlc_log_type can be one of WLC_LOG_INFO,
    WLC_LOG_WARN, WLC_LOG_ERROR or WLC_LOG_WAYLAND.

NOTES

    This callback can be configured before or after wlc_init(3) is initialised.

EXAMPLE

    #include <wlc/wlc.h>

    void logger(const char *fmt, ...); 

    static void log_handler(enum wlc_log_type type, const char *str) {
        switch (type) {
            case WLC_LOG_INFO:
            case WLC_LOG_WARN:
            case WLC_LOG_ERROR:
            case WLC_LOG_WAYLAND:
                logger("%s", str);
         }
    }

    wlc_log_set_handler(log_handler);

